16/01/2004
KUMANOVO, Macedonia -- The local campaign promoting regional co-operation within the US-Adriatic Charter kicked off in the town of Kumanovo on Thursday (15 January) with a roundtable meeting.
The campaign continues until the end of February in 14 other Macedonian towns.
It aims to inform the public about the objectives of the charter, which brings together Macedonia, Albania and Croatia in their efforts for NATO membership.
Representatives of government and the international community, local self-government, political parties, the media and NGOs will participate in a series of discussions.
(MIA, Makfax - 15/01/04)
